description: a structured classification for a diverse group of living organisms, spanning across several kingdoms and phyla

command.prompt:
Generate 3 rows for a table of a structured classification for a diverse group of living organisms, spanning across several kingdoms and phyla. The semi-colon-separated header of attributes for the table is:
Diet;Habitat;Family;Latin Name;Phylum;Class;Order;Genus;Species;Common Name;Size;Average Lifespan;Endangered Status;Native Continent

Do not generate fictional rows. Generate the rows from real known data. Here is a list of semi-colon-separated rows not to generate by semantic key only:
Common Name
African Cichlid
American Alligator
Black Widow
Convict Cichlid
Cooper's Hawk
Dogfish Shark
Domestic Dog
Earthworm
European Eel
Great White Shark
Horseshoe Crab
Sharks, Rays, Skates
Small
Virginia Opossum

Output the rows in the format of a semi-colon-separated .csv file with a column header. Then explain the source of the new data.
command.output_table:
Diet;Habitat;Family;Latin Name;Phylum;Class;Order;Genus;Species;Common Name;Size;Average Lifespan;Endangered Status;Native Continent
African Elephant;Savannas, Forests;Elephantidae;Loxodonta africana;Chordata;Mammalia;Proboscidea;Loxodonta;africana;African Elephant;10-13 ft;60-70 years;Vulnerable;Africa
Giant Panda;Bamboo Forests;Ursidae;Ailuropoda melanoleuca;Chordata;Mammalia;Ursidae;Ailuropoda;melanoleuca;Giant Panda;4-6 ft;20-30 years;Vulnerable;Asia
Bengal Tiger;Grasslands, Tropical Rainforests;Felidae;Panthera tigris tigris;Chordata;Mammalia;Felidae;Panthera;tigris;Bengal Tiger;8-10 ft;10-15 years;Endangered;Asia
